      static TaskPreemptionPolicy PP_CONTINUE_WITHOUT_RESOURCE
      The unit task will be interrupted by any task with higher priority and will be terminated (forgotten).

      Agent will not be suspended.
      static TaskPreemptionPolicy PP_NO_PREEMPTION
      The unit task cannot be interrupted by any high priority task.
      static TaskPreemptionPolicy PP_SEIZE_ANY_RESOURCE
      The unit task will be interrupted by any task with higher priority and
      will try seizing any other compatible resource.

      Agent will be suspended until there is a resource for the task execution.
      static TaskPreemptionPolicy PP_TERMINATE_SERVING
      The unit task will be interrupted by any task with higher priority and will be terminated (forgotten).

      Agent will not be suspended.
      static TaskPreemptionPolicy PP_WAIT_FOR_ORIGINAL_RESOURCE
      The unit task will be interrupted by any task with higher priority and will go into individual queue of resource unit.

      Agent will be suspended until there is a resource for the task execution.

      boolean suspendResumeEntities
      This parameter defines whether the agent whose task is suspended
      should be automatically suspended in its current flowchart block
      and automatically resumed at the time there are available resources.
      Suspend occurs because of SEIZE_ANY_RESOURCE and WAIT_FOR_ORIGINAL_RESOURCE
      preemption policy, when the resource unit owned by the agent gets grabbed by
      another task with higher priority.

      There are callbacks: "On task suspended", it is executed after auto-suspend,
      and "On task resumed", it is executed before auto-resume

      static Seize.TerminatedTaskAction TERMINATED_REMOVE_FROM_FLOWCHART
      Terminated (because of preempted resource unit) agents will be simply removed from their current place in the flowchart.

      static Seize.TerminatedTaskAction TERMINATED_SEND_TO_ENTER_BLOCK
      Terminated (because of preempted resource unit) agents will be rerouted to the given Enter block (see "Enter for terminated agents" parameter).

        public boolean seizeFromOnePool
        Seize mode:
        false = seize (alternative) resource sets
        true = seize units of the same pool

      • seizePolicy

        public SeizePolicy seizePolicy
        Defines the policy of seize:
        - Seize whole set at once - agent waits unit some set becomes fully available, and at that time it seizes all units
        - Seize units one by one - agent tries seizing units of any alternative set, once units become available. When unit is seized it may e.g. start some "preparation flowchart" while other units are not yet seized and even the resulting resource set choice is unknown (when there are alternatives).

        public boolean suspendResumeEntities
        This parameter defines whether the agent whose task is suspended
        should be automatically suspended in its current flowchart block
        and automatically resumed at the time there are available resources.
        Suspend occurs because of SEIZE_ANY_RESOURCE and WAIT_FOR_ORIGINAL_RESOURCE

        public static final TaskPreemptionPolicy PP_TERMINATE_SERVING
        The unit task will be interrupted by any task with higher priority and will be terminated (forgotten).

        Agent will not be suspended. It will just lose ALL resource units obtained in this Seize.
        Custom action may be defined using "On Task Terminated" (where the default action
        is remove agent from its current flowchart block)

      • PP_SEIZE_ANY_RESOURCE

        public static final TaskPreemptionPolicy PP_SEIZE_ANY_RESOURCE
        The unit task will be interrupted by any task with higher priority and
        will try seizing any other compatible resource.

        Agent will be suspended until there is a resource for the task execution.

      • PP_WAIT_FOR_ORIGINAL_RESOURCE

        public static final TaskPreemptionPolicy PP_WAIT_FOR_ORIGINAL_RESOURCE
        The unit task will be interrupted by any task with higher priority and will go into individual queue of resource unit.

        Agent will be suspended until there is a resource for the task execution.

      • PP_CONTINUE_WITHOUT_RESOURCE

        public static final TaskPreemptionPolicy PP_CONTINUE_WITHOUT_RESOURCE
        The unit task will be interrupted by any task with higher priority and will be terminated (forgotten).

        Agent will not be suspended. It will just lose ONLY one resource unit (which is being preempted).
        Custom action may be defined using "On Task lost unit" (where the default action
        is remove agent from its current flowchart block)

      • TERMINATED_REMOVE_FROM_FLOWCHART

        public static final Seize.TerminatedTaskAction TERMINATED_REMOVE_FROM_FLOWCHART
        Terminated (because of preempted resource unit) agents will be simply removed from their current place in the flowchart.
        User is responsible for handling the removed agent in the "On task terminated" action property.

      • TERMINATED_SEND_TO_ENTER_BLOCK

        public static final Seize.TerminatedTaskAction TERMINATED_SEND_TO_ENTER_BLOCK
        Terminated (because of preempted resource unit) agents will be rerouted to the given Enter block (see "Enter for terminated agents" parameter).
        It is also possible to execute custom actions in the "On task terminated" action property - these actions will be executed prior to sending agent to the Enter block.

      • TERMINATED_DO_NOTHING

        public static final Seize.TerminatedTaskAction TERMINATED_DO_NOTHING
        Terminated (because of preempted resource unit) agents will countinue their processing in the flowchart.
        User is responsible for taking custom actions in the "On task terminated" action property.
